THE
AERODYNAMIC
DESIGN
OF
SECTION
SHAPES
FOR
SWEPT
WINGS
AN
EXTENSION
OF
WORK
OF
LOCK
AND
ROGERS
AND
THE
RESULT
OF
COOPERATION
BY
NPL
RAE
AND
MEMBERS
OF
THE
BRITISH
AIRCRAFT
INDUSTRY
TO
ACHIEVE
A
SATISFACTORY
DESIGN
FOR
AN
AIRCRAFT
CRUISING
AT
LOW
SUPERSONIC
SPEEDS
KNOWLEDGE
OF
SHOCKWAVE
PREDICTION
ONSET
OF
WAVE
DRAG
AND
SHOCKINDUCED
SEPARATION
ALLOWS
THE
BASIC
DESIGN
TO
BE
GENERALIZED
FOR
A
WIDE
